    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-02T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-02T11:00:00-05:00" n="1"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1065</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-02T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 2, 1918—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 4, 4.22 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2339. I discussed with British Minister conversation [with]
                        <persName>Shipkoff</persName> reported under Bulgarian affairs in my 2315,
                    December 28, 7 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_512">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, Supplement 2, vol. I,
                            pp. 512</ref>–<ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_514">514</ref>.</note>
                    British Minister informs me to-day his Government telegraphed him exceedingly
                    interested in my impression concerning Bulgaria’s attitude and would be very
                    grateful if I ascertained with more distinctness how Bulgaria feels towards
                    discussion of separate peace and what arrangement might be acceptable.</p>
                <p>If Department approves, I can discreetly offer an opportunity to
                        <persName>Shipkoff</persName> and Bulgarian Minister through reliable
                    non-official to make more definite statement.<note n="2" xml:id="d1fn2">Answered
                        by telegram No. 1301, Jan. 5: “Department approves suggestion in second
                        paragraph.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
